#### [SkinnyCRUDMapper](https://github.com/skinny-framework/skinny-framework/blob/1.1.x/orm/src/main/scala/skinny/orm/SkinnyCRUDMapper.scala)
<hr/>

- Primary key should be single and long numeric
- [Finder APIs](https://github.com/skinny-framework/skinny-framework/blob/1.1.x/orm/src/main/scala/skinny/orm/feature/FinderFeature.scala)
- [Querying APIs](https://github.com/skinny-framework/skinny-framework/blob/1.1.x/orm/src/main/scala/skinny/orm/feature/QueryingFeature.scala)
- [CRUD Operation APIs](https://github.com/skinny-framework/skinny-framework/blob/1.1.x/orm/src/main/scala/skinny/orm/feature/CRUDFeature.scala)

The difference from SkinnyMapper is that insert/update/delete operations are available.

```scala
case class Member(id: Long, name: Option[String], createdAt: DateTime)
object Member extends SkinnyCRUDMapper[Member] {
  ...
}
```

The usage is like this:

```scala
// create
Member.createWithAttributes('name -> "Alice", 'createdAt -> DateTime.now)
// update
Member.updateById(123).withAttributes('name -> "Bob")
Member.updateBy(sqls.eq(Member.column.name, "Bob")).withAttributes('name -> "Bob")
// delete
Member.deleteById(123)
Member.deleteBy(sqls.eq(Member.column.name, "Alice"))
```

